<h2 id="tools-for-specific-needs">Tools for Specific Needs</h2>

<h3>Speed and Performance Auditing</h3>

<p><strong>Google PageSpeed Insights</strong> combines Lighthouse lab data with Chrome User Experience Report (CrUX) field data to give you both diagnostic information and real-world performance metrics. It is the single most authoritative source for Core Web Vitals data. Use it to audit key page templates and identify the specific resources and behaviours causing poor LCP, INP, or CLS.</p>

<p><strong>WebPageTest</strong> provides advanced testing capabilities including multi-step transactions, video comparisons, waterfall analysis, and testing from 40+ global locations on real devices and browsers. It goes deeper than PageSpeed Insights for complex performance investigations.</p>

<p><strong>GTmetrix</strong> offers a user-friendly performance testing interface with historical tracking. The free tier allows limited testing; paid plans start at $14.50/month. Best for non-technical users who need to monitor speed trends without interpreting raw Lighthouse data.</p>

<h3>Security Auditing</h3>

<p><strong>Qualys SSL Labs</strong> provides the most thorough SSL/TLS certificate analysis available, grading your configuration and identifying protocol vulnerabilities. <strong>Mozilla Observatory</strong> tests security headers and grades your configuration with specific fix recommendations. <strong>Sucuri SiteCheck</strong> scans for malware, blacklisting, and known vulnerabilities. All three are free and should be part of every security audit.</p>

<h3>Accessibility Auditing</h3>

<p><strong>WAVE</strong> (Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool) identifies accessibility issues by visually overlaying findings on your page. It catches missing alt text, contrast failures, missing form labels, and ARIA issues. <strong>axe DevTools</strong> integrates into Chrome DevTools for accessibility testing during development. Both are free and complement the accessibility checks in Lighthouse.</p>

<h3>Agency and White-Label Tools</h3>

<p>Agencies need tools that produce client-ready reports under their own branding. <strong>Semrush</strong> and <strong>SE Ranking</strong> both offer white-label PDF reports. <strong>AgencyAnalytics</strong> ($79/month+) is purpose-built for agencies, combining audit data from multiple sources into branded dashboards. For dedicated <a href="/website-audit-tools/white-label/">white-label audit tools</a>, see our detailed comparison.</p>

<h2 id="our-recommendations">Our Recommendations</h2>

<p>After testing every tool on this list across sites ranging from 10 pages to 500,000 pages, here are our recommendations for different situations.</p>

<p><strong>Solo freelancer or small business owner:</strong> Start with <strong>Screaming Frog free</strong> (if your site is under 500 pages) plus <strong>Google Search Console</strong> and <strong>PageSpeed Insights</strong>. This combination covers 80 percent of what you need at zero cost. When you outgrow the free limits, invest in the Screaming Frog paid licence at $259/year — it is the best value in the market.</p>

<p><strong>Growing agency (5-20 clients):</strong> <strong>Ahrefs</strong> or <strong>Semrush</strong> as your primary platform, supplemented by <strong>Screaming Frog</strong> for deep technical crawls. Both Ahrefs and Semrush provide the keyword, backlink, and audit data you need to serve clients comprehensively. Choose Ahrefs if backlink data is your priority; choose Semrush if client reporting and white-labelling matter more.</p>

<p><strong>Enterprise SEO team:</strong> <strong>Screaming Frog</strong> with full Google API integration, plus <strong>Ahrefs</strong> or <strong>Semrush</strong> for cloud-based monitoring. Add <strong>Sitebulb</strong> when you need to communicate technical findings to non-technical stakeholders. For very large sites, consider <strong>Lumar</strong> (formerly DeepCrawl) or <strong>Botify</strong>, which are purpose-built for enterprise-scale crawling and monitoring.</p>

<p><strong>Developer focused on performance:</strong> <strong>Lighthouse</strong> via Chrome DevTools for individual page diagnosis, <strong>WebPageTest</strong> for advanced waterfall analysis and multi-location testing, and <strong>PageSpeed Insights</strong> for real-user field data. These three free tools cover everything a developer needs to optimise Core Web Vitals.</p>

